PROBLEM WITH STP
> STP IS ENABLED ON ALL INTERFACES BY DEFAULT
> WITH MAX AGE OF 50 SECS BEFORE CONNECTING, IT'S TOO MUCH TIME BEFORE SOMEBODY CAN CONNECT A SWITCH ON THE INTERFACE

RSTP - 15 SECS, HAS NO LISTENING STATE, IT ONLY HAS LEARNING STATE


PORTFAST BPDU TOPO:





PORFAST
- TRANSITION IMMEDIATELY FROM A BLOCKING STATE INTO FORWARDING STATE
- NOT WAITING FOR LINISTENING STATE AND LEARNING STATE
- SHOULD ONLY BE CONFIGURED ON INTERFACE WHERE END DEVICES ARE CONNECTED
- BUT, WHAT IF A SWITCH IS CONNECTED TO A PORTFAST ENABLED INTERFACE?

SOLUTION:
BPDU GUARD 
- ALL INTERFACES WITH PORFAST ENABLED, SHOULD HAVE THIS CONFIGURATION.
- WHEN AN INTERFACE HAS CONFIGURATION OF PORFAST AND BPDU GUARD, WHEN A SWITCH IS CONNECTED IT WILL SET TO ERR-DISABLED STATUS TO PROVENT LOOP 


***
IT IS RECOMMENDED TO CONFIGURED PORTFAST AND BPDU GUARD


CONFIGURING PORTFAST AND BPDU GUARD
------------------------------------
SW
----
conf t 
int fa0/1
spanning-tree portfast
spanning-tree bpduguard enable
exit

